.head 3 -  ! Still need to get the My invoice routines out of loads program and into here and getting
the customer program using them instead
.head 3 +  ! Function: ProcessDeposit
.head 4 -  Description: Need to check if this customer has paid a deposit or not. If not dont  
need to do any further. When the deposit is used to pay an invoice,
we need to add a record into the cash application file with the transaction
id (the newly created one for this invoice) and the receipt key.  If the 
deposit is not fully applied eg there is still some deposit left over,
 then set the amount unapplied and fully applied flag to N.
When checking if there is an outstanding deposit, check this file first,
 anything in this file is still to be used - when have the record, check
using the receipt key whether any has already been used eg $1000 of
$2000 deposit may have already been used.  When fully used change the applied
flag to Y and move from the outstanding deposit file to the history deposit
file.  When writing the transaction record for the invoice, the transaction 
amount should be the gross total, and the deposit deducted off to give
the amount outstanding.  
.head 4 +  Returns 
.head 5 -  Boolean: 
.head 4 +  Parameters 
.head 5 -  Window Handle: hWndCalledFrom
.head 5 -  Number: nCustNo
.head 5 -  Number: nYear
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nDeposit
.head 4 -  Static Variables 
.head 4 +  Local variables 
.head 5 -  String: sWhere
.head 4 +  Actions 
.head 5 -  ! Set sgSql =  'SELECT Dep_Amount_Paid,Receipt_User_Id,Rcpt_Sysdatetime
 FROM Outstand_Deposit INTO :ngAmtPaid, :sgRcptUser, :dgRcptDateTime
 WHERE Cust_No = :nCustNo AND Dep_Year_Of_Sale = :nYear'
.head 5 -  Call CallBuildSql(  hWndCalledFrom,nSELECT, PAM_OUTSDEPSQL, OUTSTDEPOSIT, '' )
.head 5 -  Set sWhere = ' WHERE Cust_No = :nCustNo AND Dep_Year_Of_Sale = :nYear' 
.head 5 -  Set sgSql = sgSql||sWhere
.head 5 +  If SqlImmediate( sgSql )
.head 6 -  Call SqlClearImmediate(  )
.head 6 -  Set sgRcptUser = ''
.head 6 -  Call SalSendMsgToChildren( hWndCalledFrom, PAM_OUTDEPGLOBALS, 0, 0 )
.head 6 +  If sgRcptUser = ''
.head 7 -  Return TRUE
.head 5 +  Else 
.head 6 -  Call SqlClearImmediate(  )
.head 6 -  Return TRUE
.head 5 -  ! To be past here there is a record in the outstanding deposit file, we now need
to know if any has already been used
.head 5 -  Set ngUnappliedAmt = 0
.head 5 -  Set ngRcptAmt = 0
.head 5 -  Set sgSql =  'SELECT Amount_Unapplied, Receipt_Amount  FROM Cash_Receipt
 INTO :ngUnappliedAmt, :ngRcptAmt
 WHERE Receipt_User_Id = :sgRcptUser AND Rcpt_Sysdatetime = :dgRcptDateTime'
.head 5 +  If SqlImmediate( sgSql )
.head 6 -  Call SqlClearImmediate(  )
.head 6 +  If ngUnappliedAmt > 0
.head 7 -  ! Then we need to use the amount unapplied 
.head 7 -  Set nDeposit = ngUnappliedAmt
.head 6 +  Else 
.head 7 -  ! Then we need to set the deposit to the total deposit amount paid which is
the same as the receipt amount of the cash receipt record
.head 7 -  Set nDeposit = ngAmtPaid
.head 5 +  Else 
.head 6 -  Call SqlClearImmediate(  )
.head 6 -  Return TRUE
.head 5 -  ! Cant set the deposit to the invoice total if it is less than it as it hasnt been 
calculated yet, do it when extendprices is being done on the colDeposit
.head 5 -  Return TRUE
.head 3 +  ! Function: MyProcessDeposit
.head 4 -  Description: Need to check if this customer has paid a deposit or not. If not dont  
need to do any further. When the deposit is used to pay an invoice,
we need to add a record into the cash application file with the transaction
id (the newly created one for this invoice) and the receipt key.  If the 
deposit is not fully applied eg there is still some deposit left over,
 then set the amount unapplied and fully applied flag to N.
When checking if there is an outstanding deposit, check this file first,
 anything in this file is still to be used - when have the record, check
using the receipt key whether any has already been used eg $1000 of
$2000 deposit may have already been used.  When fully used change the applied
flag to Y and move from the outstanding deposit file to the history deposit
file.  When writing the transaction record for the invoice, the transaction 
amount should be the gross total, and the deposit deducted off to give
the amount outstanding.  
.head 4 +  Returns 
.head 5 -  Boolean: 
.head 4 +  Parameters 
.head 5 -  Receive Sql Handle: hSqlHdlDepAmt
.head 5 -  Receive Boolean: bHdlDepAmtConnected
.head 5 -  Receive Boolean: bHdlDepAmtPrepared
.head 5 -  !
.head 5 -  Receive Sql Handle: hSqlHdlAmtUnAplid
.head 5 -  Receive Boolean: bHdlAmtUnAplidConnected
.head 5 -  Receive Boolean: bHdlAmtUnAplidPrepared
